#: wcivf/apps/administrations/templates/elections/your_area.html:18
#: wcivf/apps/elections/templates/elections/postcode_view.html:49
msgid "Your area"
msgstr "Eich ardal"

#: wcivf/apps/administrations/templates/elections/your_area.html:20
msgid "This page lists all the parts of government that look after your area."
msgstr ""
"Mae'r dudalen hon yn rhestru'r holl rannau o'r llywodraeth sy'n gofalu am "
"eich ardal."

#: wcivf/apps/administrations/templates/elections/your_area.html:21
msgid ""
"Each of these organisations have different responsibilities and "
"representatives."
msgstr ""
"Mae gan bob un o'r sefydliadau hyn wahanol gyfrifoldebau a chynrychiolwyr."

#: wcivf/apps/administrations/templates/elections/your_area.html:26
msgid ""
"Note: you may also have a parish, town or community council in your area."
msgstr ""
"Efallai y bydd etholiadau cyngor plwyf, tref neu gymunedol mewn rhai "
"ardaloedd."

#: wcivf/apps/administrations/templates/elections/your_area.html:27
msgid "We're working on adding them to this page."
msgstr "Rydym yn gweithio ar eu hychwanegu at y dudalen hon."

#: wcivf/apps/administrations/templates/elections/your_area.html:29
msgid "Something wrong? Please "
msgstr "Rhywbeth o’i le? "

#: wcivf/apps/administrations/templates/elections/your_area.html:30
#: wcivf/apps/hustings/templates/hustings/includes/_ballot.html:14
msgid "get in touch"
msgstr "Cysylltwch â ni"

#: wcivf/apps/administrations/templates/elections/your_area.html:30
msgid "with feedback or bug reports"
msgstr "i roi adborth neu i roi gwybod am wallau"

#: wcivf/apps/administrations/templates/elections/your_area.html:33
msgid "Please pick your address"
msgstr "Dewiswch eich cyfeiriad"

#: wcivf/apps/administrations/templates/elections/your_area.html:35
msgid ""
"This postcode spans more than one area, so we need to know the address to "
"provide information about your area."
msgstr ""
"Mae’r cod post hwn ar gyfer mwy nag un ardal, felly rhaid i ni gael gwybod y "
"cyfeiriad cyn y gallwn rannu gwybodaeth am eich ardal"

#: wcivf/apps/administrations/templates/elections/your_area.html:46
msgid ""
" Sorry, we don't have any information for your postcode, or something else "
"has gone wrong. Please try a different postcode."
msgstr ""
"Nid oes gennym unrhyw wybodaeth ar gyfer eich cod post, neu mae rhywbeth "
"arall wedi mynd o'i le. Rhowch gynnig ar god post gwahanol."

#: wcivf/apps/administrations/templates/elections/your_area.html:56
msgid "Find out about local government in your area"
msgstr "Dysgwch am lywodraeth leol yn eich ardal"

#: wcivf/apps/administrations/templates/elections/your_area.html:65
#: wcivf/apps/elections/templates/elections/postcode_view.html:50
msgid ""
"As well as your new MP, there are others who represent you in your area. "
"We're working on a new experimental feature to explain who these people are "
"and how everything from your council to your police force works."
msgstr ""
"Yn ogystal â'ch AS newydd, mae eraill yn eich ardal sy'n eich cynrychioli "
"chi. Rydym yn gweithio ar nodwedd arbrofol newydd i egluro pwy yw'r bobl hyn "
"a sut mae popeth yn gweithio, e.e. eich Cyngor Lleol a’r Heddlu."

#: wcivf/apps/administrations/templates/responsibilities/org_id/parl-hoc.html:8
msgid ""
"\n"
"Members of Parliament (MPs) represent your interests and concerns in the "
"House of Commons.\n"
"\n"
"MPs consider and can propose new laws as well as raising issues that matter "
"to you in the House. This includes asking government\n"
"ministers questions about current issues including those which affect local "
"constituents.\n"
"\n"
"MPs split their time between working in Parliament itself, working in the "
"constituency that elected them and working\n"
"for their political party.\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"Mae Aelodau Seneddol (AS) yn cynrychioli eich buddiannau a'ch pryderon yn "
"Nhŷ'r Cyffredin.\n"
"Mae ASau yn ystyried ac yn cynnig deddfau newydd yn ogystal â thrafod "
"materion sy'n bwysig i chi yn y Tŷ.Mae hyn yn cynnwys holi gweinidogion y "
"llywodraeth am faterion cyfoes, gan gynnwys y rhai sy'n effeithio ar "
"etholwyr lleol.\n"
"80.\tMae ASau yn rhannu eu hamser rhwng gweithio yn y Senedd ei hun, "
"gweithio yn eu hetholaethau, a gweithio i'w plaid wleidyddol.\n"

#: wcivf/apps/administrations/templates/responsibilities/org_id/parl-hoc.html:19
msgid "Find out more about MPs"
msgstr "Dysgwch fwy am ASau"

#: wcivf/apps/administrations/templates/responsibilities/post_type/UTW.html:8
msgid ""
"\n"
"Unitary authorities are responsible for services like:\n"
"\n"
"* education\n"
"* transport\n"
"* planning\n"
"* fire and public safety\n"
"* social care\n"
"* libraries\n"
"* waste management\n"
"* trading standards\n"
"* rubbish collection\n"
"* recycling\n"
"* Council Tax collections\n"
"* housing\n"
"* planning applications\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"Mae awdurdodau unedol yn gyfrifol am wasanaethau megis:\n"
"\n"
"* addysg\n"
"* trafnidiaeth\n"
"* cynllunio\n"
"* tân a diogelwch y cyhoedd\n"
"* gofal cymdeithasol\n"
"* llyfrgelloedd\n"
"* rheoli gwastraff\n"
"* safonau masnach\n"
"* casglu sbwriel\n"
"* ailgylchu\n"
"* Casglu'r Dreth Gyngor\n"
"* tai\n"
"* ceisiadau cynllunio\n"
"\n"

#: wcivf/apps/administrations/templates/responsibilities/post_type/UTW.html:26
msgid "Understand how your council works"
msgstr "Deall sut mae eich cyngor yn gweithio"

#: wcivf/apps/administrations/templates/responsibilities/post_type/WAE.html:8
msgid ""
"\n"
"When the Senedd is sitting, Members meet twice a week in the Siambr, the "
"debating chamber, to question Welsh Government Ministers, examine proposed "
"laws, and debate various issues. Members also participate in committees that "
"focus on areas such as health and education, examining laws and government "
"policies that could impact these sectors. These committees are composed of "
"Members reflecting the overall representation of the elected parties.\n"
"\n"
"Most Members have a local office in their constituency or region, employing "
"staff to assist with constituent enquiries. They hold regular 'surgeries' "
"where the public can meet with their representatives to discuss concerns. "
"Additionally, Members engage with constituents online or over the phone, and "
"visit businesses, schools, and local organisations to gain insight into "
"everyday issues, which they may later address in the Senedd.\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"Pan fo’r Senedd wedi ymgynnull, mae'r Aelodau'n cyfarfod ddwywaith yr "
"wythnos yn y Siambr, sef y siambr drafod, i holi Gweinidogion Llywodraeth "
"Cymru, i edrych ar ddeddfau arfaethedig, ac i drafod materion amrywiol. Mae "
"aelodau hefyd yn cymryd rhan mewn pwyllgorau sy'n canolbwyntio ar wahanol "
"feysydd, gan gynnwys iechyd ac addysg, ac yn edrych ar gyfreithiau a "
"pholisïau'r llywodraeth a allai effeithio ar y sectorau hyn. Mae'r "
"pwyllgorau hyn yn cynnwys Aelodau sy'n adlewyrchu cynrychiolaeth gyffredinol "
"y pleidiau etholedig.\n"
"Mae gan y rhan fwyaf o'r Aelodau swyddfa leol yn eu hetholaeth neu ranbarth, "
"ac mae’r swyddfa’n cyflogi staff i gynorthwyo gydag ymholiadau etholiadol. "
"Maen nhw'n cynnal 'cymorthfeydd' rheolaidd lle gall y cyhoedd gwrdd â'u "
"cynrychiolwyr i drafod pryderon. Bydd Aelodau hefyd yn cysylltu ag etholwyr "
"ar-lein neu dros y ffôn, ac yn ymweld â busnesau, ysgolion a sefydliadau "
"lleol i gael dealltwriaeth o’r materion bob dydd y gallan nhw roi sylw iddyn "
"nhw yn y Senedd yn ddiweddarach.\n"

